"{\"uid\": \"hollywoodreporter.com-news-general-news-tom-cruise-skydive-paris-olympics-closing-ceremony-1235964594\", \"text\": \"Subscribe for full access to The Hollywood Reporter  Subscribe for full access to The Hollywood Reporter  Another planned stunt in Los Angeles that would have been part of the same 2028 handoff segment was scrapped over LAPD traffic concerns and California Coastal Commission permitting issues.  ByGary Baum  Senior Writer  Tom Cruisewill reportedly have a starring role in the Paris 2024 Olympic Games' Aug. 11 closing ceremony, when he may skydive to the Hollywood Sign during the orchestrated handoff to Los Angeles for the 2028 Olympiad. According toTMZ, the stuntwas quietly shotin March.  Cruise has attended the Paris games, including for the women's gymnastics qualifiers as well as swimming competitions. \\\"It's awesome,\\\" hetoldReuters. \\\"Great stories, great athletes. It's incredible what they have to do, the sense of accomplishment.\\\"Related StoriesMovies'Spartacus: House of Ashur' Creator, Star Talk Pushing Boundaries of Sex and Violence, Intimacy Coordinators and Not Changing the Written WordMovies\\\"The Villagers Were the Key to Making This Film Happen\\\": 'THR Presents' Q&A With 'Sun Never Again' Director David Jovanovic  Production company Fulwell 73 - co-run by James Corden and known for Hulu'sThe Kardashiansas well as Adele's 2021 CBS specialOne Night Only, which took place at the iconic Griffith Observatory - is behind the L.A. segment, which will mix prerecorded and live elements.  The Hollywood Reporterhas learned that an early plan involved a large party at Will Rogers State Beach, where the handoff of the Olympic flag would occur. This was scrapped due to LAPD concerns over an extended Pacific Coast Highway shutdown and challenges obtaining the necessary California Coastal Commission permitting. Fulwell 73 did not respond to a request for comment.  The Paris Games' July 26opening ceremony, featuring a performance by Lady Gaga, drag queens and global athletes sailing down the River Seine, drewmixedreactions.  Closing ceremonies and their handoffs have previously been the stage for celebrity spectacles. At Beijing in 2008, Jimmy Page and Leona Lewis collaborated on a performance of Led Zeppelin's \\\"Whole Lotta Love\\\" while atop a faux busheadedto London.  The 1984 Los Angeles Summer Olympic Games opening and closing ceremonies - produced byRootsmastermind David L. Wolper and key Walt Disney Co. creative executive Robert Jani - were notably Hollywood-driven spectacles, including performances by Lionel Richie, The Beach Boys and film composer John Williams.  Sign up for THR news straight to your inbox every day  Subscribe for full access to The Hollywood Reporter  Send us a tip using our anonymous form.\"}"